<LP>
   PFIZER Inc. (New York) -- This pharmaceutical and health
care company named Barry M. Bloom, 61 years old, to the new
post of Pfizer senior vice president, research and
development, effective Sept. 1. Succeeding Mr. Bloom as
president of the Central Research division is John F.
Niblack, 51. Mr. Bloom also had been a vice president of the
parent; Mr. Niblack, currently executive vice president of
Central Research, will be nominated as a vice president of
Pfizer. His successor as executive vice president at Central
Research hasn't been named.
